A secret map sets the blue-bodied, white-panted mini men (and woman) on a race to find a legend in a first full trailer for &#8220;Smurfs: The Lost Village.&#8221;Rebooting a film franchise that saw outings in 2011 and 2013, its April 2017 entry &#8220;Smurfs: The Lost Village&#8221; sees the miniature blue people set off on a new adventure.The trailer promises plenty of accessible humor as a troupe of Smurfs sneak out of their own village in search of another.At the same time, their enemy Gargamel is also on the lost village&#8217;s trail and the Smurfs already have a lot to contend with when they venture outside the safety of their own homeland.-Relaxnews